<br>
This is sort of where I started writing my Kizoku no Yashiki series…so you can understand there are huge similarities, which is why I need some help reinventing the idea.<br>
<br>
The original story was about a man who helps create a drug to make the better soldier (to surpass the exoskeletal gear designs that are in testing right now, in the 21st century) and is driven mad by the drug to the point where he rapidly becomes either a demon or an angel (final <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> organic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> evolution, just before becoming an incorporeal being, or a godlike spirit, which cannot be achieved by anything in existance). KuroiChikara (Kizoku no Yashiki Book One) involved the same storyline, but the drug's purpose was for space travel, and the side effects were activated by the death of the main character's fianceé (and becoming a freak was influenced by massive bodily harm).<br>
<br>
So………basically, I want to keep the evolutionary aspect of the story, but I want a different form of catalyst. I need a different reason for this person's evolutionary advantage, but it can't be a drug, and it has to be surrealistic in some way (not some unexplainable amulet or item of some sort, I need something based on religion, science, etc.)<br>
<br>
Also, the two evolutionary perfections have been designed a thousand times over, but I tend to like the draconian design (derived from the FF Ultimate and Omega Weapons) for the angel, and I'm still undecided on the demon design as of yet, but I'm attracted to a chimera design (reptilian/insect/mammal with human skeletal characteristics) <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
